# Atelier : ArgoCD D√©ploiement

## Objectif
Utiliser ArgoCD pour le d√©ploiement GitOps sur AKS


## √âtape 1 : Installer ArgoCD (10 min)

### 1.1 Cr√©er le namespace
```bash
kubectl create namespace argocd
```

### 1.2 Installer ArgoCD
```bash
kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml

# Attendre que tous les pods soient pr√™ts
kubectl wait --for=condition=ready pod --all -n argocd --timeout=300s
```

### 1.3 Installer ArgoCD CLI
```bash
# Linux
VERSION=$(curl --silent "https://api.github.com/repos/argoproj/argo-cd/releases/latest" | grep '"tag_name"' | sed -E 's/.*"([^"]+)".*/\1/')
curl -sSL -o argocd-linux-amd64 https://github.com/argoproj/argo-cd/releases/download/$VERSION/argocd-linux-amd64
sudo install -m 555 argocd-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/argocd
rm argocd-linux-amd64

# macOS
brew install argocd

# V√©rifier l'installation
argocd version --client
```

### 1.4 Exposer ArgoCD Server
```bash
# Option 1: Port Forward (pour test)
kubectl port-forward svc/argocd-server -n argocd 8080:443 &

# Option 2: LoadBalancer (recommand√© pour production)
kubectl patch svc argocd-server -n argocd -p '{"spec": {"type": "LoadBalancer"}}'

# Attendre l'IP externe
kubectl get svc argocd-server -n argocd -w
```

### 1.5 R√©cup√©rer le mot de passe initial
```bash
ARGOCD_PASSWORD=$(kubectl -n argocd get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret \
  -o jsonpath="{.data.password}" | base64 -d)

echo "ArgoCD Admin Password: $ARGOCD_PASSWORD"
```

### 1.6 Se connecter √† ArgoCD
```bash
# Via LoadBalancer
ARGOCD_SERVER=$(kubectl get svc argocd-server -n argocd \
  -o jsonpath='{.status.loadBalancer.ingress[0].ip}')

# Ou via port-forward
ARGOCD_SERVER="localhost:8080"

# Login
argocd login $ARGOCD_SERVER --username admin --password $ARGOCD_PASSWORD --insecure

# Changer le mot de passe
argocd account update-password
```

---

## √âtape 2 : Pr√©parer le repository GitOps (15 min)

### 2.1 Cr√©er la structure du repository
```bash
mkdir -p argocd-demo
cd argocd-demo

# Structure GitOps
mkdir -p {apps,infrastructure,projects}/{base,overlays/{dev,staging,production}}
```

### 2.2 Cr√©er l'application de base
```bash
# Base application
cat <<'EOF' > apps/base/deployment.yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: demo-app
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: demo-app
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: demo-app
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        image: nginxdemos/hello:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 64Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 100m
            memory: 128Mi
EOF

cat <<'EOF' > apps/base/service.yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: demo-app
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: demo-app
  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 80
EOF

cat <<'EOF' > apps/base/kustomization.yaml
apiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1
kind: Kustomization

resources:
  - deployment.yaml
  - service.yaml

commonLabels:
  managed-by: argocd
EOF
```

### 2.3 Cr√©er les overlays pour chaque environnement
```bash
# Dev overlay
cat <<'EOF' > apps/overlays/dev/kustomization.yaml
apiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1
kind: Kustomization

namespace: dev

bases:
  - ../../base

replicas:
  - name: demo-app
    count: 1

namePrefix: dev-

commonLabels:
  environment: dev
EOF

# Staging overlay
cat <<'EOF' > apps/overlays/staging/kustomization.yaml
apiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1
kind: Kustomization

namespace: staging

bases:
  - ../../base

replicas:
  - name: demo-app
    count: 2

namePrefix: staging-

commonLabels:
  environment: staging
EOF

# Production overlay
cat <<'EOF' > apps/overlays/production/kustomization.yaml
apiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1
kind: Kustomization

namespace: production

bases:
  - ../../base

replicas:
  - name: demo-app
    count: 3

namePrefix: prod-

commonLabels:
  environment: production

patchesStrategicMerge:
  - patches.yaml
EOF

cat <<'EOF' > apps/overlays/production/patches.yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: demo-app
spec:
  template:
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: app
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 100m
            memory: 128Mi
          limits:
            cpu: 200m
            memory: 256Mi
EOF
```

### 2.4 Initialiser Git et pousser
```bash
# Initialiser Git
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial GitOps structure"

# Cr√©er un repository sur GitHub
# Remplacer <YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME> par votre nom d'utilisateur
GITHUB_USER="<YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME>"
GITHUB_REPO="argocd-demo"

# Cr√©er le repo via GitHub CLI (si install√©)
gh repo create $GITHUB_REPO --public --source=. --remote=origin --push

# Ou manuellement:
# 1. Cr√©er le repo sur github.com
# 2. Ex√©cuter:
git remote add origin https://github.com/$GITHUB_USER/$GITHUB_REPO.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```

