## √âtape 7 : Tester le GitOps workflow (10 min)

### 7.1 Modifier l'application dans Git
```bash
cd argocd-demo

# Modifier le nombre de replicas en dev
cat <<'EOF' > apps/overlays/dev/kustomization.yaml
apiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1
kind: Kustomization

namespace: dev

bases:
  - ../../base

replicas:
  - name: demo-app
    count: 3  # Chang√© de 1 √† 3

namePrefix: dev-

commonLabels:
  environment: dev
EOF

# Commit et push
git add .
git commit -m "Scale dev to 3 replicas"
git push
```

### 7.2 Observer la synchronisation automatique
```bash
# Attendre quelques secondes
sleep 10

# V√©rifier que ArgoCD a d√©tect√© le changement
argocd app get demo-app-dev

# Voir les pods
kubectl get pods -n dev

# Observer dans l'UI ArgoCD
```

### 7.3 Tester un changement en production (sync manuel)
```bash
# Modifier la production
cat <<'EOF' > apps/overlays/production/kustomization.yaml
apiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1
kind: Kustomization

namespace: production

bases:
  - ../../base

replicas:
  - name: demo-app
    count: 5  # Chang√© de 3 √† 5

namePrefix: prod-

commonLabels:
  environment: production

patchesStrategicMerge:
  - patches.yaml
EOF

# Commit et push
git add .
git commit -m "Scale production to 5 replicas"
git push
```

### 7.4 Synchroniser manuellement la production
```bash
# Via CLI
argocd app sync demo-app-production

# Ou via UI: cliquer sur "Sync" dans l'interface

# V√©rifier
kubectl get pods -n production
```

