## √âtape 10 : Configurer les notifications (8 min)

### 10.1 Cr√©er un ConfigMap pour les notifications
```bash
cat <<EOF | kubectl apply -f -
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: argocd-notifications-cm
  namespace: argocd
data:
  service.slack: |
    token: \$slack-token
  
  template.app-deployed: |
    message: |
      Application {{.app.metadata.name}} is now running new version.
      Sync Status: {{.app.status.sync.status}}
      Health Status: {{.app.status.health.status}}
  
  template.app-health-degraded: |
    message: |
      Application {{.app.metadata.name}} has degraded.
      Health Status: {{.app.status.health.status}}
  
  trigger.on-deployed: |
    - when: app.status.operationState.phase in ['Succeeded']
      send: [app-deployed]
  
  trigger.on-health-degraded: |
    - when: app.status.health.status == 'Degraded'
      send: [app-health-degraded]
EOF
```

### 10.2 Cr√©er un Secret pour Slack (optionnel)
```bash
# Si vous avez un token Slack
kubectl create secret generic argocd-notifications-secret \
  --from-literal=slack-token=<YOUR_SLACK_TOKEN> \
  -n argocd
```

### 10.3 Ajouter des annotations aux applications
```bash
kubectl patch app demo-app-dev -n argocd --type merge -p '{
  "metadata": {
    "annotations": {
      "notifications.argoproj.io/subscribe.on-deployed.slack": "deployments",
      "notifications.argoproj.io/subscribe.on-health-degraded.slack": "alerts"
    }
  }
}'
```

