## √âtape 12 : Monitoring et troubleshooting (5 min)

### 12.1 Voir les logs ArgoCD
```bash
# Application controller
kubectl logs -n argocd deployment/argocd-application-controller -f

# Repo server
kubectl logs -n argocd deployment/argocd-repo-server -f

# Server
kubectl logs -n argocd deployment/argocd-server -f
```

### 12.2 V√©rifier le statut de sync
```bash
# Toutes les applications
argocd app list

# D√©tails d'une application
argocd app get demo-app-dev --refresh

# Voir les ressources d√©ploy√©es
argocd app resources demo-app-dev

# Voir les diff√©rences
argocd app diff demo-app-dev
```

### 12.3 Forcer une synchronisation
```bash
# Sync complet
argocd app sync demo-app-dev

# Sync avec prune
argocd app sync demo-app-dev --prune

# Hard refresh (ignore cache)
argocd app get demo-app-dev --hard-refresh
```

