## Bonus : Best Practices GitOps

### 1. Structure de repository
```
repository/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ apps/                    # Applications
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ base/               # Configuration de base
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ overlays/           # Environnements sp√©cifiques
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ infrastructure/         # Infrastructure (ingress, monitoring)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ base/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ overlays/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ projects/               # ArgoCD AppProjects
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ applicationsets/        # ApplicationSets
```

### 2. Strat√©gie de branches
- **main**: Production
- **staging**: Staging
- **develop**: Development

### 3. Promotion entre environnements
```bash
# Script de promotion
#!/bin/bash
# promote.sh

SOURCE_ENV=$1
TARGET_ENV=$2

echo "Promoting from $SOURCE_ENV to $TARGET_ENV"

# Copier la configuration
cp -r apps/overlays/$SOURCE_ENV/* apps/overlays/$TARGET_ENV/

# Commit et push
git add apps/overlays/$TARGET_ENV/
git commit -m "Promote from $SOURCE_ENV to $TARGET_ENV"
git push

# Sync ArgoCD
argocd app sync demo-app-$TARGET_ENV

# Utilisation:
# ./promote.sh dev staging
# ./promote.sh staging production
```

### 4. Sealed Secrets avec ArgoCD
```bash
# Installer Sealed Secrets
kubectl apply -f https://github.com/bitnami-labs/sealed-secrets/releases/download/v0.24.0/controller.yaml

# Cr√©er un sealed secret
kubectl create secret generic my-secret \
  --from-literal=password=supersecret \
  --dry-run=client -o yaml | \
  kubeseal -o yaml > sealed-secret.yaml

# Commiter dans Git
git add sealed-secret.yaml
git commit -m "Add sealed secret"
git push
```

